Lingua::IT::Hyphen - Italian word hyphenation

The module exports one function, sillaba(), which gets one or
more text strings and returns an array of syllabes.

Example:

    use Lingua::IT::Hyphen;
    print join('-', sillaba "Salve, mondo!"));
        
    Sal-ve-mon-do
    
Aldo Calpini <dada@divinf.it>
05 April 1999


